2. In these Regulations, unless the context otherwise requires- Interpretation
"appropriate fee" means the fee prescribed by the Minister in exercise of his
powers contained in section twenty one of the Act;
"draw net" means any net ordinarily used for encircling and hauling fish onto a
shallow bank for capture;
"gill net" means a multifilament twine net customarily left drifting or stationary in
water and which captures fish by meshing;
"kutumpula" means any fishing method whereby fish are driven into a stationary gill
net or monofilament net;
"licence" means a fishing licence issued under regulation 3;
"monofilament net" means any net made of a single solid filament material for the
web of a net.
